The police in Mahwelereng outside Mokopane are searching
for 71-year-old Johanna Mosima Malapile. She went missing on Wednesday, last week, when she left
her home in Ga-Chokoe village outside Mapela in Limpopo, to go buy beverages at
a local tavern at around 15:30. Police spokesperson Constable Maphure Manamela said the
matter was then brought to the attention of the Police by her family on Friday. The police appeal to anyone with information about the
whereabouts of this victim to contact Captain Petrus Nkhumane at 076 917 7747
or the police emergency toll free number 08600 10111 or the sms crime line
32211.They may also contact the nearest police station.